		<h2 id="research">Research</h2>

<p>I enjoy building networked systems that address practical problems, with strong architectural and theoretical foundations.  You can check out my <a href="papers/">complete list of papers</a>.  My group is currently working in several main areas:</p>

<ul>

    <li><b>Low latency networking:</b> We're leading <a href="https://nsf-breaking-low-agora.illinois.edu/">Project Agora</a>, a $7.1M NSF Breaking Low project to develop deployable low-latency wireless networking, and demonstrate its use for XR-based medical collaboration. Our other projects include the <a href="papers/index.html#cisp">Speed of Light Internet</a>, <a href="papers/index.html#sentosa23dchannel">DChannel</a>, <a href="papers/index.html#touseef23hvc">HVCs</a>, and <a href="papers/index.html#vaddiraju25wtsn">WTSN for low latency WiFi</a>.</li>

    <li><b>Machine learning for systems:</b> Our group is part of the <a href="https://ldos.utexas.edu">LDOS NSF Expeditions In Computing</a> project, which is building a clean-slate Learning Directed Operating System. We've also worked on online learning for congestion control (<a href="papers/index.html#jay19aurora">Aurora</a> and <a href="http://pccproject.net">PCC</a>), deep learning as an <a href="papers/index.html#gilad19robustifying">adversary</a>, and performance diagnosis (<a href="papers/index.html#harsh23murphy">Murphy</a>).</li>

    <li><b>Service layer networking</b> to optimize, observe, and secure communication between microservices. See news article: <a href="https://siebelschool.illinois.edu/news/nsf-microservices">CS-led team pioneers improvement of microservice-based applications</a> and our HotNets 2021 paper which put forth a vision of <a href="papers/index.html#ashok21servicemeshes">Service meshes as a new network layer</a>. We've built Service Layer Traffic Engineering (SLATE) (<a href="index.html#lim24slate">in HotNets 2024</a> and to appear in NSDI 2026), <a href="papers/index.html#ashok23traceweaver">TraceWeaver: Distributed Request Tracing for Microservices Without Application Modification</a>, and <a href="papers/index.html#grewal23microservice-policies">expressive policies for microservices</a>.</li>

    <li><b>Network verification and formal methods:</b> Our group pioneered network verification, specifically building the first data plane verifier applied to a real network (<paper-link pid="mai11anteater">Anteater</paper-link>) and the first real-time data plane verifier (<paper-link pid="khurshid13veriflow">VeriFlow</paper-link>), which led to our startup Veriflow, now part of VMware. We've worked on customizable consistency properties (<paper-link pid="zhou15ccg">CCG</paper-link>),	fast configuration verification (<a href="papers/index.html#prabhu20plankton">Plankton</a>), <a href="papers/index.html#liu-kheradmand20selfdriving">verifying self-driving infrastructure</a>, verifying systems of multiple microservice controllers (<paper-link pid="liu24kivi">Kivi</paper-link>), expressive policies for microservices (<paper-link pid="grewal23microservice-policies">HotNets 2023</paper-link> and <paper-link pid="grewal25safetree">SafeTree in OOPSLA 2025</paper-link>), and automated reasoning for network architectures (<paper-link pid="bothra24archie">HotNets 2024</paper-link>).</li>
    
</ul>

<p>Other areas of work recently and in the past include:</p>

<ul>
    <li>Data center network topology, specifically the Jellyfish expander graph (<paper-link pid="singla12jellyfish">NSDI 2012</paper-link>, <paper-link pid="singla14throughput">NSDI 2014</paper-link>), measuring and understanding throughput (<paper-link pid="jyothi16throughput">SC 2016</paper-link>), spineless data centers (<paper-link pid="harsh20spineless">HotNets 2020</paper-link>), Starfish (to appear in NSDI 2026)</li>
	<li>Network diagnosis, including including network fault localization (<a href="papers/index.html#harsh23flock">Flock</a>) and diagnosing performance problems in distributed apps (<a href="papers/index.html#harsh23murphy">Murphy</a>)</li>
    <li>Compact routing and fast shortest path algorithms in social networks</li>
    <li>Flexible Internet architectures</li>
    <li>Peer-to-peer systems</li>
</ul>

